# Cursor rules: Conductor (opt-in)

Apply Conductor ONLY when the user explicitly asks to "Start a new track", "Use Conductor", "Create conductor track", "Update plan", or "Execute plan".

On Conductor opt-in:
- If `.conductor/CONDUCTOR.md` exists in this repo, read it and follow it as the authoritative Conductor protocol.
- If `.conductor/CONDUCTOR.md` does not exist, tell the user Conductor is not installed in this repo and instruct them to install it with `conductor init`.

When not opted-in:
- Behave normally.
